race.description: 13 February Hannam Vale Cup Day Championship Hcp (C4)
race.comment: GET SOME FUN (2) consistent mare racing in a rich vein of form. Proved too strong in a deep contest with a sound neck victory over 1300m at this track. Will spear across again and prove hard to hold out in this tougher test. LIFE COACH (1) talented gelding who doesn't have to improve much to win this. Game return from the long break when a narrow sixth over 1200m at Gosford. Comes to hand quickly and not without top-three prospects. SAVVYROCKER (3) is on a quick backup after going back from the wide draw when a plugging seventh over 1200m at Port Macquarie. Tempo suits and will appreciate the weight relief. BABY RYAN (4) flying under the radar this time in and deserves his chance in this company. Closed late from back in the field with a narrow third over 1305m at Coffs Harbour. Brings the right figures to play a leading role.
